%20is%20to%20drink%20water%2C%20wear%20sunscreen%2C%20and%20use%20retinol.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20there's%20a%20lot%20of%20ambiguity%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20shopping%20for%20retinol.%20Which%20versions%20of%20it%20are%20effective%2C%20and%20which%20are%20masquerading%20as%20effective%3F%20How%20often%20should%20you%20apply%20it%3F%20Why%20does%20it%20cause%20irritation%3F%20How%20long%20do%20you%20have%20to%20use%20it%20before%20you%20see%20results%3F%20Can%20you%20mix%20it%20with%20lotion%3F%20Do%20some%20products%20%26quot%3Bcancel%20out%26quot%3B%20the%20benefits%20of%20retinol%20if%20mixed%20together%3F%20And%20on%20and%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20asked%20four%20dermatologists%20%E2%80%94%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mdcsnyc.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDr.%20Dendy%20Engelman%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20MDCS%20Dermatology%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tareendermatology.com%2Foffice%2Fdr-mohiba-tareen%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDr.%20Mohiba%20Tareen%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20Tareen%20Dermatology%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jasonemermd.com%2F%3Futm_source%3DGMBlisting%26utm_medium%3Dorganic%26utm_campaign%3Dgmb%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDr.%20Jason%20Emer%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sperlingdermatology.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDr.%20Shari%20Sperling%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20Sperling%20Dermatology%2C%20and%20a%20medical%20aesthetician%20with%2010%20years%20of%20experience%20as%20a%20facialist%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthelafacialist.com%2Fabout-me%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECandace%20Marino%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20to%20answer%20the%20most%20common%20retinol%20FAQs.%20Find%20all%20the%20answers%20below.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c0486491-5fa2-470e-82cc-38cbd9926096%5C%22%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22What%20is%20retinol%3F%5C%22%3EWhat%20is%20retinol%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ERetinol%20is%20a%20form%20of%20pure%20vitamin%20A%2C%20which%20is%20used%20in%20skincare%20to%20combat%20signs%20of%20aging.%20As%20we%20age%2C%20we%20lose%20vitamin%20A%2C%20and%20this%20depletion%20contributes%20to%20the%20normal%20signs%20of%20aging.%20Retinol%20is%20used%20to%20reverse%20and%20further%20prevent%20that%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22464976fc-43dc-4857-bf43-01a069740363%5C%22%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22What%20does%20retinol%20do%3F%5C%22%3EWhat%20does%20retinol%20do%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Dr.%20Engelman%2C%20%26quot%3BRetinol%2C%20and%20especially%20retinoic%20acid%2C%20work%20to%20increase%20cell%20turnover%2C%20build%20collagen%2C%20improve%20discoloration%2C%20hydrate%20skin%20and%20reduce%20acne%20by%20replenishing%20the%20body%20of%20vitamin%20A.%26quot%3B%20And%2C%20according%20to%20Dr.%20Tareen%2C%20%26quot%3BRetinol%20is%20the%20only%20applied%20topical%20agent%20that%20has%20been%20shown%20to%20actually%20stimulate%20collagen%20and%20plump%20the%20skin%20due%20to%20the%20formation%20of%20new%20blood%20vessels.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETechnically%2C%20retinol%20is%20just%20one%20of%20the%20many%20different%20types%20of%20retinoids.%20(Retinoid%20is%20the%20catchall%20phrase%20for%20A-based%20formulas).%20You'll%20see%20the%20name%20retinoic%20acid%20in%20prescription%20products%2C%20and%20names%20like%20retinol%20and%20retinaldehyde%20in%20over-the-counter%20(OTC)%20products.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f773f0c4-59d7-4886-b10b-b73083504b1b%5C%22%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22What%20are%20the%20best%20over-the-counter%C2%A0retinol%C2%A0creams%3F%5C%22%3EWhat%20are%20the%20best%20over-the-counter%C2%A0retinol%C2%A0creams%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20strongest%20retinol%20creams%2C%20like%20Tretinoin%2C%20will%20require%20a%20prescription.%20But%2C%20if%20you're%20looking%20for%20over-the-counter%20(OTC)%20options%20as%20a%20cost-effective%2