m%2F%3FamazonTrackingID%3Dbi-auto-15117152898evj-20%26h%3Db17d769a15c375c5ba94f232663db37335076caa8d7bb6cdb3848189bf2bf9f6%26postID%3D61b8efdbf2a36b1ac9f49067%26postSlug%3Dguides%252Fbeauty%252Fretinol-faqs%26tags%3Dservice%253Acapi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fulta.ztk5.net%252Fc%252F196318%252F164999%252F3037%253Fu%253Dhttps%25253A%25252F%25252Fwww.ulta.com%25252Facne-treatment-gel%25253FproductId%25253DxlsImpprod15791005%5C%22%20data-autoaffiliated%3D%5C%22true%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUlta%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It%20used%20to%20require%20a%20prescription%20but%20was%20approved%20for%20over-the-counter%20sale%20by%20the%20FDA%20in%202016.%20It's%20the%20OTC%20retinol%20product%20many%20dermatologists%20will%20recommend%20for%20patients%20who%20count%20acne%20and%20scarring%20in%20their%20primary%20concerns%20because%20it%20includes%20Adapalene%2C%20which%20is%20designed%20to%20treat%20acne.%20%26quot%3BDifferin%20Gel%20Contains%20a%20powerful%20retinoid%20to%20clear%20acne%20and%20prevent%20future%20ones%26quot%3B%20explained%20Dr.%20Engelman%2C%20%26quot%3Bas%20well%20as%20to%20prevent%20acne%20scarring.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDr.%20Engelman%20also%20recommends%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%2F%3FamazonTrackingID%3Dbi-auto-15117152898evj-20%26h%3D32dc3292a2cf5578e6e2c85cdd24de30769b05847eb98f089b1298b86730b233%26postID%3D61b8efdbf2a36b1ac9f49067%26postSlug%3Dguides%252Fbeauty%252Fretinol-faqs%26tags%3Dservice%253Acapi%26u%3Dhttp%253A%252F%252Fulta.ztk5.net%252Fc%252F196318%252F164999%252F3037%253Fu%253Dhttps%25253A%25252F%25252Fwww.ulta.com%25252Fretinol-ceramide-capsules-line-erasing-night-serum%25253FproductId%25253Dpimprod2000303%2526amp%253Bsubid2%253D1584649726380at8pfqr4t%2526amp%253BsubId3%253Dxid%253Afr1584649732263dgd%5C%22%20data-autoaffiliated%3D%5C%22true%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EElizabeth%20Arden%20Retinol%20Ceramide%20Capsules%20(%2484)%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0as%20the%20best%20OTC%20retinol%20option%20for%20dry%20skin.%20%26quot%3BThese%20are%20incredible%20for%20dry%20skin.%20They're%20formulated%20with%20ceramides%2C%20which%20help%20to%20hydrate%20the%20skin%20and%20can%20combat%20some%20of%20the%20irritating%20and%20drying%20effects%20that%20retinols%20have%20on%20the%20skin.%20Additionally%2C%20they%20have%20olive%2C%20sunflower%2C%20and%20avocado%20oils%20in%20the%20formula%2C%20so%20they%20add%20additional%20hydration%20to%20the%20skin%20while%20providing%20all%20of%20the%20benefits%20of%20topical%20retinol.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EOther%20well-known%20options%20recommended%20by%20Dr.%20Emer%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22a38e7499-7050-4141-9348-2de874bcbdc1%5C%22%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22How%20should%20you%20layer%20your%20retinol%20products%20on%20the%20skin%3F%5C%22%3EHow%20should%20you%20layer%20your%20retinol%20products%20on%20the%20skin%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EDermatologists%20are%20still%20a%20bit%20divided%20on%20this%20question%2C%20but%20a%20clear%20majority%20recommend%20starting%20with%20your%20thinnest%20consistency%20product%20and%20moving%20to%20the%20thickest.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDr.%20Engelman%20recommends%20the%20following%20order%20(based%20on%20consistency)%3A%20start%20with%20products%20like%20toning%20water%2C%20followed%20by%20serums%20and%20ampoules.%20Next%2C%20apply%20any%20prescription%20topical%20treatments%20(like%20retinol)%2C%20then%20lotions%2C%20creams%2C%20and%20finally%20sunscreen%20at%20the%20end.%20If%20you're%20applying%20multiple%20serums%2C%20start%20with%20the%20thinnest.%20You%20should%20also%20allow%20each%20layer%20to%20be%20fully%20absorbed%20before%20applying%20the%20next%20one%2C%20which%20will%20probably%20only%20take%20about%2030%20seconds%20to%20one%20minute.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStart%20with%20a%20clean%20face%20and%2C%20if%20you%20want%20to%20be%20extra%20strategic%2C%20apply%20products%20when%20your%20skin%20is%20damp.%20%26quot%3BYour%20skin%20will%20be%20more%20pliable%20than%20dry%20skin%2C%26quot%3B%20Engelman%20explains%2C%20%26quot%3Band%20this%20allows%20%5Bthe%20product%5D%20to%20penetrate%20deeper.%26quot%3B%20But%2C%20if%20your%20skin%20is%20still%20acclimating%20to%20retinol%20and%20especially%20sensitive%2C%20Dr.%20Sperling%20recommends%20washing%20your%20face%2C%20waiting%2030%20minutes%2C%20and%20then%20applying%20it.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you're%20especially%20sensitive%20to%20reintol%2C%20Dr.%20Tareen%20recommends%20using%20the%20%26quot%3Bsandwich%20technique%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20applying%20a%20light%20layer%20of%20moisturizer%20first%2C%20followed%20by%20the%20retinoid%2C%20and%20then%20another%20layer%20of%20moisturizer%20only%20in%20the%20places%20where%20your%20skin%20typically%20gets%20dry.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELayering%20products%20correctly%20is%20important%20if%20you%20want%20your%20products%20to%20work.%20If%20you%20place%20one%20product%20on%20your%20skin%2C%20like%20a%20serum%2C%20and%20follow%20up%20with%20another%20product%20whose%20molecules%20are%20smaller%20than%20the%20first%2C%20like%20a%20toner%2C%20then%20the%20second%20product%20cannot%20penetrate%20the%20first%20layer.%20The%20serum's%20large%20molecules%20will%20essentially%20%26quot%3Block%20out%26quot%3B%20the%20molecules%20of%20the%20moisturizer.%20So%2C%20if%20you've%20already%20applied%20the%20serum%2C%20skip%20the%20toner%20%E2%80%94%20you're%20just%20wasting%20the%20product.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3ESee%20more%3A%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fbeauty%2Fbest-face-moisturizer%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20best%20face%20moisturizers%20for%20every%20skin%20type%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cbr%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%228551f399-07d2-4e3e-9fa1-7a983360b6c6%5C%22%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22What%20percentage%20of%20retinol%20should%20you%20use%3F%C2%A0%5C%22%3EWhat%20percentage%20of%20retinol%20should%20you%20use%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EUnless%20your%20dermatologist%20prescribes%20more%2C%20stick%20to%20formulas%20with%201%25%20retinol%20or%20less.%20According%20to%20Dr.%20Emer%2C%20%26quot%3BYou%20may%20want%200.25%25%20when%20first%20starting%20out%2C%20then%20increase%20slowly%20to%200.5%20and%20then%20to%201.0%20overtime.%C2%A0%20Switch%20up%20strengths%20every%20two%20to%20four%20weeks%20when%20exfoliation%20and%20irritation%20are%20tolerable.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f3be5c5e-6163-4751-97cb-5d2444ca734f%5C%22%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22Which%20iterations%20of%20retinol%20are%20effective%20and%20which%20aren't%3F%5C%22%3EWhich%20iterations%20of%20retinol%20are%20effective%20and%20which%20aren't%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAll%20derivatives%20of%20Vitamin%20A%20are%20effective%2C%26quot%3B%20Dr.%20Engelman%20explained.%20%26quot%3B%5Bbut%5D%20they%20vary%20on%20effectiveness.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20work%20quickly%2C%20the%20vitamin%20A%20ingredient%20needs%20to%20be%20closest%20to%20its%20active%20form%20(retinoic%20acid)%2C%20which%20is%20what%20you'll%20find%20in%20prescription%20retinol%20creams.%20OTC%20options%20are%20often%20a%20few%20steps%20removed%20from%20retinoic%20acid%2C%20which%20is%20why%20they%20take%20longer%20to%20work.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20weakest%20version%20is%20retinyl%20palmitate%20(it%20has%20to%20convert%20first%20to%20retinol%2C%20then%20to%20retinaldehyde%2C%20then%20to%20retinoic%20acid)%2C%20according%20to%20Marino.%20It%20may%20be%20good%20for%20people%20who%20have%20hypersensitive%20or%20very%20dry%20skin%2C%20but%2C%20if%20you%20want%20something%20stronger%2C%20then%20you'll%20want%20to%20find%20something%20with%20retinaldehyde%20in%20it%2C%20since%20it's%20one%20step%20closer%20to%20retinoic%20acid.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDr.%20Emer%20advises%20avoiding%20Retinyl%20acetate%2C%20Retinyl%20propionate%2C%20and%20Retinyl%20palmitate%3B%20the%20body%20does%20not%20convert%20enough%20of%20it%20to%20retinoic%20acid%20for%20it%20to%20be%20very%20helpful.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20also%20recommended%20that%20if%20you%20have%20sensitive%20skin%2C%20you%20don't%20combine%20active%20products%20like%20benzoyl%20peroxide%2C%20sulfur%2C%20resorcinol%20or%20salicylic%20acid%2C%20which%20are%20often%20found%20in%20acne%20treatments.%20The%20combination%20can%20increase%20irritation%20and%20decrease%20retinol's%20efficacy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3ERead%20more%3A%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fbeauty%2Fdifferin-acne-gel-review%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20acne%20gel%20that%20used%20to%20require%20a%20prescription%20is%20now%20on%20Amazon%20for%20%2425%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2296f336a3-1f53-4bfa-b300-1404efc4d564%5C%22%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22How%20often%20do%20you%20need%20to%20use%C2%A0retinol%C2%A0to%20see%20results%3F%5C%22%3EHow%20often%20do%20you%20need%20to%20use%C2%A0retinol%C2%A0to%20see%20results%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EGenerally%2C%20it%20takes%20a%20few%20weeks%20to%20see%20results%2C%20but%20some%20OTC%20options%20may%20require%20months%20of%20regular%20use.%20Most%20dermatologists%20said%20you'll%20need%20to%20use%20retinol%20for%20a%20few%20weeks%20before%20you%20see%20results%2C%20but%20you%20should%20see%20improvements%20by%2012%20weeks%20with%20most%20products.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2239efd0cd-7650-41b7-8cbb-dac2b18378d5%5C%22%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22How%20often%20should%20you%20apply%20your%C2%A0retinol%C2%A0creams%3F%5C%22%3EHow%20often%20should%20you%20apply%20your%C2%A0retinol%C2%A0creams%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20beginning%2C%20Dr.%20Engelman%2C%20Dr.%20Tareen%2C%20Dr.%20Sperling%2C%20and%20Marino%20recommend%20starting%20out%20by%20applying%20a%20retinol%20one%20to%20two%20nights%20per%20week%20to%20build%20up%20your%20skin's%20tolerance.%20Then%2C%20increase%20your%20frequency%20to%20every%20other%20night%2C%20as%20you%20can%20tolerate%20it.%20The%20goal%20is%20to%20eventually%20train%20your%20skin%20to%20use%20it%20nightly.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20using%20retinol%20creams%2C%20you%20may%20experience%20some%20dryness%20and%20sensitivity%2C%20but%20not%20necessarily.%20%26quot%3BThis%20adjustment%20phase%20is%20known%20as%20Retinization%2C%26quot%3B%20Marino%20explained.%20%26quot%3BDuring%20this%20phase%2C%20one%20can%20expect%20dryness%2C%20flakiness%20and%20mild%20redness%2C%20which%20is%20caused%20by%20the%20retinol's%20breakdown%20of%20dead%20surface%20cells.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20sensitive%20skin%20can%20be%20%26quot%3Btrained%26quot%3B%20to%20tolerate%20retinol%2C%20according%20to%20Dr.%20Engelman.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3ESee%20more%3A%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fbeauty%2Fbest-exfoliator%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20best%20facial%20exfoliators%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22550bd9e6-01f9-43d9-8065-827a5a57c8d6%5C%22%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22How%20long%20does%20it%20take%20for%20your%20skin%20to%20adjust%20to%20retinol%3F%5C%22%3EHow%20long%20does%20it%20take%20for%20your%20skin%20to%20adjust%20to%20retinol%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EUsually%2C%20most%20people's%20skin%20will%20adjust%20within%20six%20to%2012%20weeks%2C%20according%20to%20Dr.%20Tareen.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BCell%20turnover%20is%20typically%2021-28%20days%2C%26quot%3B%20Dr.%20Emer%20explains.%20%26quot%3BWith%20retinol%2C%20it%20can%20be%20increased%20to%20a%207-14%20day%20shed.%20So%2C%20in%20general%2C%20it%20takes%20two%20to%20six%20weeks%20for%20your%20skin%20to%20get%20used%20to%20retinol.%20Redness%2C%20irritation%20and%20flaking%20are%20normal%20for%20that%20period%2C%20as%20well%20as%20when%20you%20increase%20in%20strength%20(as%20you%20progress)%20or%20when%20you%20combine%20with%20actives%20like%20glycolic%20acid%20or%20salicylic%20acid%20(if%20you%20have%20acne)%20or%20hydroquinone%20(if%20you%20have%20pigmentation).%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22ddd91f65-cb0c-4eb1-ac11-b41ffbdc418b%5C%22%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22Can%20you%20mix%C2%A0retinol%C2%A0with%20lotion%20when%20applying%3F%5C%22%3ECan%20you%20mix%C2%A0retinol%C2%A0with%20lotion%20when%20applying%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20order%20to%20get%20the%20best%20effects%2C%20Dr.%20Tareen%20recommends%20not%20diluting%20your%20retinol%20by%20mixing%20it%20with%20lotion.%20If%20you%20need%20to%2C%20she%20recommends%20applying%20layers%20of%20moisturizer%20instead.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20wrong%20to%20mix%20in%20moisturizer%2C%20just%20less%20effective.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%2C%20Dr.%20Tareen%20and%20Dr.%20Emer%20agree%20that%20you%20shouldn't%20mix%20retinol%20with%20certain%20ingredients.%20If%20your%20lotion%20has%20alpha-hydroxy%20acids%20or%20benzoyl%20peroxide%20in%20it%20(commonly%20found%20in%20acne-fighting%20products)%20then%20you%20may%20not%20want%20to%20mix%20the%20two.%20They%20can%20make%20retinol%20less%20effective%20and%20may%20worsen%20irritation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2226b4fd47-6b56-4a8c-8f88-10f263868a59%5C%22%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22How%20much%C2%A0retinol%C2%A0should%20you%20apply%3F%5C%22%3EHow%20much%C2%A0retinol%C2%A0should%20you%20apply%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EEach%20dermatologist%20advised%20using%20a%20pea-sized%20amount%2C%20or%20just%20slightly%20more%20than%20that%20to%20cover%20your%20entire%20face.%20Dr.%20Tareen%20recommends%20dispensing%20a%20pea-sized%20amount%20to%20the%20back%20of%20your%20hand%20and%20then%20taking%20a%20drop%20of%20that%20to%20the%20forehead%2C%20nose%2C%20cheeks%2C%20and%20chin%20%E2%80%94%20and%20then%20connecting%20the%20dots%20by%20rubbing%20it%20in%20gently.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20don't%20stop%20the%20benefits%20at%20just%20your%20face.%20Dr.%20Engelman%20and%20Dr.%20Emer%20recommend%20placing%20a%20thin%20layer%20over%20the%20face%2C%20neck%2C%20chest%2C%20and%20even%20hands.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3ERead%20more%3A%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fbeauty%2Fbest-acne-treatment%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20best%20acne%20treatments%20for%20bumps%20and%20blemishes%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2214f7fdb7-9398-464c-92b0-ac0b37e381e7%5C%22%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22Does%20retinol%20expire%3F%C2%A0%5C%22%3EDoes%20retinol%20expire%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EYes.%20You'll%20want%20to%20check%20the%20date%20on%20your%20tube%20before%20use.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%227e6331a7-b71c-4ffa-a038-78afb822d98b%5C%22%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22Does%20retinol%20help%20acne%3F%5C%22%3EDoes%20retinol%20help%20acne%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EYes%2C%20retinol%20is%20the%20best%20medication%20for%20most%20acne%2C%20Dr.%20Tareen%20explained.%20%26quot%3BRetinol%20is%20the%20only%20medication%20that%20affects%20the%20four%20causative%20actors%20of%20acne%3A%20P.%20acnes%20bacteria%2C%20inflammation%2C%20sebum%20production%2C%20and%20keratinization%20(over-growth%20of%20dead%20skin%20cells).%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDr.%20Emer%20points%20to%20its%20exfoliating%20powers%20for%20opening%20and%20cleaning%20out%20the%20pores%2C%20as%20well%20as%20decreasing%20oil%20production%20and%20inflammation.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2287bef6d2-497f-4535-9dbd-95b3281a900e%5C%22%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22Does%20retinol%20lighten%20the%20skin%3F%5C%22%3EDoes%20retinol%20lighten%20the%20skin%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ENo.%20Retinol%20does%20not%20affect%20the%20melanocytes%20(pigment-producing%20cells)%2C%20according%20to%20Dr.%20Tareen.%20%26quot%3BThe%20skin%20can%20look%20brighter%20with%20routine%20retinol%20use%20because%20of%20the%20normalization%20of%20the%20skin%20barrier%20and%20because%20your%20skin%20looks%20more%20even%20with%20fewer%20blemishes.%20Skin%20also%20looks%20rosier%20with%20retinol%20use%20because%20retinol%20turns%20on%20the%20production%20of%20good%20blood%20vessels%20in%20the%20skin.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225a24abc6-b478-4413-a862-c82ae11aeb7c%5C%22%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22Does%20retinol%20thin%20the%20skin%3F%5C%22%3EDoes%20retinol%20thin%20the%20skin%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EYes%20and%20no.%20Retinols%20do%20thin%20the%20outer%20layer%20of%20the%20skin%20(the%20stratum%20corneum)%2C%20but%2C%20according%20to%20Dr.%20Tareen%20and%20Marino%2C%20that's%20one%20of%20their%20advantages.%20%26quot%3BAs%20we%20age%2C%20the%20outer%20stratum%20corneum%20can%20get%20dull%20and%20rough.%20So%20we%20want%20retinols%20to%20thin%20the%20stratum%20corneum%20so%20that%20skin%20can%20look%20smoother%20and%20more%20polished.%26quot%3B%20Dr.%20Tareen%20explained.%20%26quot%3BRetinols%20actually%20thicken%20the%20dermis%20(the%20collagen%20packed%20layer%20of%20the%20skin)%20so%20you%20look%20plump%20and%20fresh.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20thinner%20outermost%20layer%20also%20helps%20your%20products%20penetrate%20deeper.%20%26quot%3BRetinol%20is%20going%20to%20exfoliate%20the%20stratum%20corneum%20-%20the%20outermost%20layer%20of%20the%20epidermis%20which%20is%20comprised%20of%20dead%20skin%20cells.%26quot%3B%20Marino%20said.%20%26quot%3BIn%20doing%20this%20you're%20allowing%20better%20product%20penetration%20to%20ensure%20proper%20hydration%20since%20your%20hydrating%20products%20aren't%20working%20through%20the%20dead%20barrier.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3ESee%20more%3A%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fbeauty%2Fbest-retinol-eye-cream%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20best%20retinol%20eye%20cream%20you%20can%20buy%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2281f307f9-f6de-4397-9416-799854b293b9%5C%22%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22Does%20retinol%20help%20with%20acne%20scars%3F%5C%22%3EDoes%20retinol%20help%20with%20acne%20scars%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EYes%2C%20though%20not%20drastically.%20By%20stimulating%20collagen%20and%20thickening%20the%20dermis%2C%20retinols%20help%20to%20fade%20pits%20left%20by%20past%20acne%2C%20according%20to%20Dr.%20Tareen%20and%20Dr.%20Sperling%2C%20but%20Dr.%20Emer%20notes%20that%20the%20effects%20will%20be%20minimal.%20%26quot%3BIt%20can%20make%20the%20texture%20of%20the%20skin%20appear%20smoother%2C%20but%20scarring%20%5Boften%5D%20requires%20more%20deep%20treatments%20like%20lasers%2C%20peels%2C%20fillers%2C%20subcision%2C%20etc.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%222a124b9a-c831-46b2-b9be-c6dbf2dafb42%5C%22%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22Do%20the%20results%20last%20if%20you%20stop%20using%C2%A0retinol%3F%5C%22%3EDo%20the%20results%20last%20if%20you%20stop%20using%C2%A0retinol%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EYes%2C%20but%20most%20dermatologists%20say%20you'll%20want%20to%20resume%20using%20it%20for%20optimal%20results.%20%26quot%3BRetinols%20help%20turn%20back%20the%20clock.%20If%20you%20have%20to%20stop%20them%20(for%20example%20while%20pregnant)%2C%20your%20skin%20is%20still%20better%20from%20the%20time%20you%20were%20using%20them%2C%26quot%3B%20explains%20Dr.%20Tareen.%20%26quot%3B%5Bbut%5D%20best%20to%20re-start%20your%20retinol%20again%20when%20you%20can.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20dermatologists%20recommend%20using%20it%20at%20least%20twice%20weekly%20to%20see%20results.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22a54c4376-01d0-4aff-971c-029ec93e1b1d%5C%22%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22Can%20retinol%20cause%20harm%3F%5C%22%3ECan%20retinol%20cause%20harm%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EYes%2C%20retinol%20can%20be%20harmful%20if%20you%20are%20pregnant%20or%20using%20it%20too%20frequently%20before%20building%20up%20a%20tolerance.%20If%20you're%20pregnant%20and%20looking%20for%20an%20alternative%2C%20Marino%20recommends%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%2F%3FamazonTrackingID%3Dbi-auto-15117152898evj-20%26h%3De3f8548dd4b038ed32dbd0cbde0fb6c882777ed4eb5b0183a4fe8005a5d019b6%26postID%3D61b8efdbf2a36b1ac9f49067%26postSlug%3Dguides%252Fbeauty%252Fretinol-faqs%26tags%3Dservice%253Acapi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.anrdoezrs.net%252Flinks%252F6415797%252Ftype%252Fdlg%252Fhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.dermstore.com%252Fproduct_Active%252BSerum_10787.htm%253Fgclid%253DEAIaIQobChMIs_vIvdCn6AIVkZOzCh18cgBhEAYYASABEgKAjvD_BwE%2526amp%253Bscid%253Dscplp10787%2526amp%253Bsc_intid%253D10787%2526amp%253Biv_%253D__iv_p_1_g_105743645744_c_424622113669_w_pla-491281737744_n_g_d_c_v__l__t__r__x_pla_y_6790012_f_online_o_10787_z_US_i_en_j_491281737744_s__e__h_9067609_ii__vi__%2526amp%253Butm_source%253Dfro%2526amp%253Butm_medium%253Dpaid_search%2526amp%253Butm_term%253Dskin%252Bcare%2526amp%253Butm_campaign%253D500480%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EActive%20Serum%20by%20iS%20Clinical%20(%24138)%3C%2Fa%3E%20which%20features%20a%20multi-acid%20complex%20to%20accelerate%20cellular%20turnover%20as%20a%20temporary%20alternative.%20Dr.%20Engelman%20mentioned%20Bakuchiol%2C%20%26quot%3Ban%20antioxidant%20that%20has%20been%20proven%20to%20help%20with%20oxidative%20stress%2C%20as%20well%20as%20acne.%20It%20mimics%20vitamin%20E%20to%20help%20heal%20and%20hydrate%20the%20skin.%20It%20is%20antibacterial%20so%20it%20helps%20to%20regulate%20breakouts.%20Lastly%2C%20it%20protects%20the%20cell%20from%20oxidative%20stress%20by%20regulating%20the%20mitochondria.%20This%20limits%20cell%20damage%20from%20free%20radicals%20and%20therefore%20combats%20aging.%26quot%3B%20Bakuchiol%20was%20popularly%20used%20in%20Beautycounter's%20line%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%