ides%2Fbeauty%2Fretinol-faqs%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Why%20some%20Social%20Security%20offices%20are%20temporarily%20closed%20across%20the%20US%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%227277%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22people%20step%20into%20a%20social%20security%20office%20in%20new%20york%20city%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69e93819a98bc8fdc096dab3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225299%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESome%20Social%20Security%20offices%20are%20temporarily%20closed.%3Cp%3EZhang%20Fengguo%2FXinhua%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EA%20slew%20of%20Social%20Security%20offices%20are%20closed%20due%20to%20staffing%20and%20facility%20issues.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ERural%20beneficiaries%20may%20be%20more%20affected%20by%20closures%2C%20with%20some%20closed%20offices%20staffed%20by%20just%20one%20worker.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20SSA%20workforce%20has%20shrunk%20by%2012%25%20in%20the%20wake%20of%20DOGE%20efficiency%20cuts.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ESocial%20Security%20beneficiaries%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsocial-security-offices-doge-cutting-most-customer-service-workers-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eseeking%20in-person%20help%3C%2Fa%3E%20might%20encounter%20new%20obstacles%20%E2%80%94%20including%20faulty%20HVAC%20systems.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ssa.gov%2Fagency%2Femergency%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMore%20than%20a%20dozen%3C%2Fa%3E%20Social%20Security%20field%20offices%20are%20listed%20as%20closed%20to%20in-person%20service%2C%20instead%20directing%20customers%20to%20reach%20out%20by%20phone%20or%20contact%20the%20national%20800%20number.%20Now%2C%20the%20list%20of%20closures%20has%20prompted%20concerns%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsocial-security-retirement-customer-service-office-doge-cuts-ssa-trump-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ethe%20beleaguered%20agency%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fretired-seniors-scared-economy-social-security-administration-doge-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eits%20recipients%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20federal%20employees'%20union%20memo%20obtained%20by%20Business%20Insider%20sheds%20some%20light%20on%20why%20offices%20are%20closed%3A%20Some%20due%20to%20operational%20issues%20with%20their%20buildings%2C%20while%20others%20are%20so%20small%20that%20any%20understaffing%20forces%20them%20to%20temporarily%20shut%20down.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETwo%20offices%20%E2%80%94%20located%20in%20Bloomsburg%2C%20Pennsylvania%2C%20and%20Logan%2C%20West%20Virginia%20%E2%80%94%20are%20closed%20due%20to%20%26quot%3Bfacility%20issues.%26quot%3B%20One%20in%20Detroit%20Park%2C%20Michigan%2C%20is%20closed%20due%20to%20ongoing%20HVAC%20issues%3B%20that%20office%20has%20previously%20closed%20due%20to%20mold%20and%20water%20intrusion.%20Another%20in%20Fort%20Walton%2C%20Florida%2C%20is%20being%20repaired%20after%20a%20fire%2C%20per%20the%20memo.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20closures%20come%20at%20a%20tumultuous%20time%20for%20the%20Social%20Security%20Administration%20and%20its%20beneficiaries%3B%20the%20agency%20shed%20around%207%2C000%20workers%2C%20or%20nearly%2012%25%20of%20its%20workforce%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdoge-wait-times-social-security-solvency-what-retirees-should-know-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eduring%20the%20DOGE%20era%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20has%20had%20to%20temporarily%20reassign%20some%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsocial-security-field-staff-reassigned-phones-call-wait-data-vanishes-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eemployees%20to%20staff%20phone%20lines%3C%2Fa%3E.%20While%20the%20SSA%20said%20these%20office%20closures%20are%20temporary%2C%20staffing%20issues%20and%20a%20lack%20of%20field%20offices%20could%20be%20an%20increasing%20problem%20for%20the%20administration%20and%20recipients%20alike.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Caside%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHave%20a%20tip%3F%20Contact%20these%20reporters%20via%20Signal%20at%20julianakaplan.33%20and%20alliekelly.10%2C%20or%20email%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Ajkaplan%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ejkaplan%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Aallisonkelly%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eallisonkelly%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Use%20a%20personal%20email%20address%20and%20a%20nonwork%20device%3B%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finsider-guide-to-securely-sharing-whistleblower-information-about-powerful-institutions-2021-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_self%5C%22%3E%20here's%20our%20guide%20to%20sharing%20information%20securely%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Faside%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESome%20currently-shuttered%20offices%20simply%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsocial-security-checks-staff-firings-office-closures-trump-federal-workers-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Edon't%20have%20enough%20staff%3C%2Fa%3E.%20These%20smaller%20offices%2C%20called%20resident%20stations%2C%20are%20often%20staffed%20by%20just%20one%20person%20and%20serve%20low-population%20areas.%20Two%20resident%20stations%20in%20rural%20Montana%20and%20Wyoming%20are%20closed%20for%20lack%20of%20workers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThese%20resident%20stations%20are%20a%20really%20important%20part%20of%20the%20way%20that%20we%20ensure%20that%20folks%2C%20particularly%20in%20rural%20areas%2C%20get%20access%20to%20services%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Molly%20Weston%20Williamson%2C%20a%20senior%20fellow%20at%20the%20left-leaning%20Center%20for%20American%20Progress%20who's%20been%20tracking%20Social%20Security%20staffing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20station%20in%20Decorah%2C%20Iowa%20is%20currently%20closed%20because%20its%20last%20remaining%20worker%20retired%20over%20the%20summer%2C%20and%20the%20staffer%20who%20had%20been%20filling%20in%20returned%20to%20their%20home%20office%20during%20the%20October%20shutdown.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOver%20the%20last%20decade%20and%20a%20half%2C%20we%20have%20not%20gotten%20any%20kind%20of%20meaningful%20sustained%20hiring%20to%20replace%20the%20aging%20SSA%20workforce%20and%20to%20actually%20meet%20public%20demand%20as%20the%20baby%20boomers%20began%20to%20reach%20their%20retirement%20age%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Jessica%20LaPointe%2C%20a%20council%20president%20for%20the%20federal%20workers'%20union%20and%20longtime%20SSA%20employee.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20car%20is%20rattling%20down%20the%20highway%20leaking%20more%20and%20more%20fuel%20every%20day%20%E2%80%94%20and%20that%20fuel%20is%20people%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Martin%20O'Malley%2C%20former%20commissioner%20of%20SSA%20under%20President%20Joe%20Biden.%20%26quot%3BGhost%20offices%20are%20happening%20with%20greater%20and%20greater%20frequency.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22ef1dfe89-796f-496e-99bf-ccb6a1f15489%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ELosing%20'a%20lifeline'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20a%20rural%20office%20is%20closed%2C%20local%20residents%20don't%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsocial-security-policy-changes-harder-to-claim-benefits-retirement-trump-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ehave%20many%20options%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Sometimes%20paperwork%20or%20identification%20needs%20to%20be%20done%20in%20person%2C%20or%20older%20adults%20have%20questions%20that%20are%20more%20easily%20answered%20by%20a%20trained%20employee%20they%20can%20talk%20to.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20field%20office%20closures%20listed%20on%20the%20Social%20Security%20website%20are%20not%20permanent.%20The%20offices%20are%20temporarily%20closed%20or%20providing%20limited%20service%20due%20to%20planned%20renovations%2C%20required%20maintenance%2C%20or%20facilities%20issues%20that%20we%20are%20actively%20working%20to%20resolve%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20agency%20said%20in%20a%20statement%20to%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BSSA's%20resident%20stations%20are%20located%20in%20rural%20locations%20and%20typically%20have%20one%20or%20two%20employees%20assigned%20to%20provide%20in-person%20services%20on%20a%20limited%20basis.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELaPointe%20said%20she%20worries%20about%20beneficiaries%20in%20small%20towns%20that%20lost%20their%20office%20and%20may%20not%20have%20easy%20access%20to%20the%20internet%20or%20a%20phone.%20Some%20of%20the%20offices%20have%20been%20closed%20for%20over%20a%20year%20without%20a%20clear%20reopening%20timeline%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThose%20resident%20stations%20are%20vital%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BThey're%20often%20in%20rural%20areas%20of%20the%20country%2C%20where%20they%20are%20a%20lifeline%20for%20people%20in%20the%20surrounding%20communities.%20If%20they%20close%20down%2C%20beneficiaries%20might%20have%20to%20travel%20hundreds%20of%20miles%26quot%3B%20to%20another%20office.%20A%20report%20published%20in%202025%20by%20the%20Center%20for%20Budget%20and%20Policy%20Priorities%20found%20that%20six%20million%20Social%20Security%20beneficiaries%20already%20live%20more%20than%2045-miles%20from%20the%20nearest%20field%20office.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20temporary%20shutterings%20follow%20years%20of%20stretched-thin%20funding%20at%20the%20agency.%20Employee%20numbers%20recently%20hit%20a%2050-year%20low.%20LaPointe%20said%20that%20both%20hiring%20and%20retention%20are%20%26quot%3Bin%20crisis%26quot%3B%20and%20struggling%20to%20compete%20with%20the%20private%20sector.%20Hundreds%20of%20SSA%20staff%20members%20were%20recently%20reassigned%20from%20field%20offices%20to%20the%20800%20customer%20service%20line%2C%20and%20Business%20Insider%20previously%20reported%20that%2041%20(largely%20rural)%20offices%20lost%20more%20than%2025%25%20of%20their%20workers%20due%20to%20DOGE%20cuts%20last%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Foig.ssa.gov%2Fassets%2Fuploads%2F032517.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESSA%20has%20previously%20said%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20staff%20reshuffling%20and%20an%20AI%20chatbot%20feature%20on%20the%20agency%20website%20are%20intended%20to%20fill%20these%20gaps%20and%20ensure%20beneficiaries%20receive%20their%20checks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20if%20closures%20are%20temporary%20or%20waiting%20on%20needed%20repairs%2C%20service%20issues%20may%20extend%20beyond%20just%20a%20shuttered%20door.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWrit%20large%2C%20we%20also%20know%20that%20there%20are%20plenty%20of%20offices%20across%20the%20country%20where%20the%20doors%20are%20open%2C%20they're%20not%20shut%20down%2C%20but%20folks%20are%20experiencing%20really%20significant%20delays%2C%26quot%3B%20Williamson%20said.%20%26quot%3BFolks%20are%20having%20real%20trouble%20getting%20the%20appointments%20they%20need.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-social-security-offices-temporarily-closed-across-us-2026-4%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1776955630000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69e93852367066d7c296fd95%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-social-security-offices-temporarily-closed-across-us-2026-4%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20number%20of%20Social%20Security%20offices%20across%20the%20US%20are%20closed%20due%20to%20staffing%20shortages%20and%20facility%20issues.%20Here's%20what's%20causing%20the%20disruptions.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22jkaplan%40businessinsider.com%20(Juliana%20Kaplan%2CAllie%20Kelly)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-social-security-offices-temporarily-closed-across-us-2026-4%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Hackers%