%20wasn't%20making%20much%20and%20struggled%20to%20adapt.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EI%20found%20it%20hard%20to%20make%20friends%20and%20didn't%20have%20much%20money%20to%20spend%20on%20hobbies.%20Then%2C%20I%20lost%20my%20job.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EAfter%20getting%20a%20new%2C%20higher-paying%20job%20in%20a%20different%20town%2C%20Colorado%20began%20to%20feel%20like%20home.%20%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EA%20Google%20search%20was%20all%20it%20took%20to%20convince%20me%20to%20move%20from%20Miami%20to%20rural%20Colorado.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJust%20before%20graduating%20from%20college%2C%20I%20applied%20for%20a%20program%20that%20pairs%20early-career%20journalists%20with%20publications%20in%20areas%20that%20need%20extra%20news%20coverage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20program%20matched%20me%20with%20a%20listing%20in%20a%20small%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoved-nyc-suburb-to-rural-town-biggest-surprises-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ecommunity%20near%20the%20mountains%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20just%20a%20few%20pictures%20I%20found%20online%20of%20the%20area%2C%20with%20snowcapped%20peaks%20in%20the%20background%20and%20plenty%20of%20green%20space%2C%20had%20me%20sold.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThings%20didn't%20go%20how%20I%20expected%20%E2%80%94%20and%20I%20almost%20left%20%E2%80%94%20but%20just%20about%20three%20years%20later%2C%20Colorado%20is%20starting%20to%20feel%20like%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%229c1290a5-b16d-48e4-932d-5eb3973c2dc3%5C%22%3ELiving%20in%20a%20rural%20small%20town%20was%20quite%20an%20adjustment%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222261%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22snowy%20hills%20in%20Colorado%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69e63976a98bc8fdc096c6cc%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221696%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ELearning%20to%20snowboard%20helped%20me%20feel%20at%20home%20in%20Colorado.%3Cp%3EKylea%20Henseler%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20first%2C%20I%20felt%20like%20I%20had%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-its-like-living-canadian-town-movies-filmed-victoria-hallmark%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Emoved%20into%20a%20Hallmark%20movie%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20town%20itself%20had%20just%20around%201%2C000%20residents%2C%20a%20few%20restaurants%2C%20the%20only%20stoplight%20for%20dozens%20of%20miles%2C%20and%20a%20grocery%20store%20so%20expensive%20I%20drove%2045%20minutes%20to%20the%20nearest%20city%20to%20shop%20instead.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20bright%20side%2C%20the%20lack%20of%20restaurants%20and%20affordable%20groceries%20forced%20me%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-cook-and-bake-better-at-home%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ebecome%20a%20much%20better%20cook%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20I%20learned%20skills%20I%20carry%20with%20me%20to%20this%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20community%20was%20also%20beautiful%2C%20with%20walking%20paths%2C%20a%20mountain-bike%20trail%20network%2C%20stunning%20views%20of%20the%20mountains%2C%20and%20easy%20access%20to%20activities%20like%20hiking%20and%20even%20rock%20and%20ice%20climbing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20night%2C%20the%20skies%20were%20so%20dark%20you%20could%20see%20every%20star.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20I%20moved%20here%20from%20Miami%2C%20I%20didn't%20even%20mind%20not%20having%20the%20Florida%20city's%20bustling%20nightlife.%20Really%2C%20I%20just%20struggled%20to%20socialize%20with%20anyone%20close%20to%20my%20age%20at%20all%20for%20the%20first%20year%20I%20lived%20in%20Colorado.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20of%20the%20neighbors%20in%20my%20small%20town%20seemed%20to%20be%20at%20least%20twice%20my%20age.%20It%20wasn't%20easy%20for%20me%20to%20find%20activities%20or%20third%20spaces%20where%20I%20could%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmaking-new-friends-like-dating-need-to-weed-through-duds-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Emeet%20other%20people%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20their%2020s%2C%20either%20%E2%80%94%20even%20the%20closest%20affordable%20gym%20was%20nearly%20an%20hour%20away%20from%20my%20apartment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlthough%20the%20promise%20of%20adventure%20lured%20me%20to%20Colorado%2C%20I%20quickly%20realized%20getting%20into%20most%20activities%20I%20was%20interested%20in%2C%20like%20snowboarding%2C%20wasn't%20feasible%20on%20my%20small%20paycheck.%20On%20top%20of%20that%2C%20I%20didn't%20have%20many%20local%20friends%20to%20try%20them%20with.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWithin%20a%20year%2C%20I%20had%20found%20myself%20thousands%20of%20miles%20from%20everyone%20I%20knew%20and%20was%20hardly%20getting%20by.%20Then%2C%20I%20found%20out%20I%20was%20about%20to%20lose%20my%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2262ec20da-e9c7-47a1-9603-6102275d4e38%5C%22%3EHaving%20to%20find%20a%20new%20role%20shook%20things%20up%2C%20but%20it%20helped%20me%20make%20the%20most%20of%20my%20new%20home%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22woman%20smiling%20with%20friends%20in%20redrock%20amphitheater%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69e639153fecbb42897a1a59%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221701%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EI%20lived%20in%20Colorado%20for%20three%20years%20before%20finally%20visiting%20the%20iconic%20Red%20Rocks%20Amphitheater.%3Cp%3EKylea%20Henseler%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAbout%20eight%20months%20after%20starting%20the%20job%20that%20brought%20me%20to%20Colorado%2C%20my%20bosses%20told%20me%20they%20weren't%20renewing%20my%20contract%20for%20the%20next%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20first%2C%20I%20freaked%20out.%20I'd%20agreed%20the%20job%20was%20a%20poor%20fit%2C%20but%20it%20was%20a%20%3Cem%3Ejob%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20and%20there%20weren't%20many%20others%20in%20my%20field%20nearby.%20I%20considered%20leaving%20the%20area.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELuckily%2C%20soon%20after%20I%20got%20the%20news%2C%20there%20was%20an%20opening%20for%20a%20feature%20reporter%20in%20the%20closest%20nearby%20city%2C%20which%20is%20home%20to%20about%2020%2C000%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20already%20familiar%20with%20it%20from%20driving%20there%20multiple%20times%20per%20week%20to%20work%20out%20and%20buy%20groceries%2C%20and%20although%20it's%20still%20a%20fairly%20small%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoving-off-grid-what-its-like-challenges-benefits-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Etight-knit%20community%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20it%20had%20a%20lot%20more%20things%20to%20do%20and%20people%20to%20meet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20job%20was%20a%20better%20fit%2C%20as%20I%20got%20to%20work%20on%20the%20kind%20of%20outdoor%2C%20culture%2C%20and%20feature%20writing%20I'd%20always%20enjoyed.%20It%20paid%20more%2C%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFinally%2C%20with%20a%20higher%20paycheck%20and%20more%20access%20to%20activities%20and%20people%2C%20I%20started%20making%20the%20most%20out%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fliving-in-colorado-after-traveling-to-all-50-states%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eliving%20in%20Colorado%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMaking%20friends%20was%20a%20struggle%20at%20first%2C%20but%20I%20had%20more%20places%20to%20try%20doing%20so%20in%20my%20bigger%20town.%20I%20also%20realized%20many%20others%20were%20in%20the%20same%20boat%20as%20me%2C%20so%20if%20I%20met%20girls%20close%20to%20my%20age%20(especially%20if%20they%20were%20also%20new%20to%20town)%2C%20I'd%20ask%20them%20out%20to%20coffee%20and%20say%20I%20was%20trying%20to%20make%20friends.%20Most%20of%20the%20time%2C%20so%20were%20they.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20also%20took%20advantage%20of%20third%20spaces%2C%20like%20the%20gym%2C%20to%20keep%20myself%20busy%20and%20social.%20And%20once%20I%20felt%20financially%20stable%2C%20I%20splurged%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbest-tips-first-time-skiing-snowboarding-expert-advice%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Esnowboarding%20gear%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20took%20advantage%20of%20a%20free%20